Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.80,0:00:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He\Nsorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.20,0:00:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to cover\Nthis thing. Seems loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.32,0:01:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of the spiritual uh\Ntrip
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.76,0:01:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because that has not covered to my\Nsatisfaction anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.56,0:01:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the challenges that arise\Nthe traps that uh lay there and wake
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.79,0:01:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning which many of you have\Nalready experienced there's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.20,0:01:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,chaotic disturbance\NYou think that when you become a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual aspirant, you're going to walk\Naround feeling holy and this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.72,0:01:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,boom,\Ncataclysmic changes, major changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.64,0:01:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk out on whole situations and walk\Naway from a fortune of a corporation and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,say goodbye.\NWhat are you taking with you? Well, a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.68,0:01:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hammer and pair of screwdrivers and pair\Nof shorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.52,0:01:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God will take care of the rest. And God\Ndoes. And um as you're driving down your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.52,0:02:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,truck and you say to your buddy, you\Nknow what we need is a pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.64,0:02:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just then you look over on the right and\Nthere's a pair of pliers laying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.52,0:02:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Such things happen all the time.\NSo you don't need anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.80,0:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can walk out with nothing.\NNothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the universe provides all that you\Nneed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over again.\NAll right. So that's devotional faith
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.40,0:02:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll get to later. I don't want\Nto get to that because I won't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep talking too well.\NWe call it devotional non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.92,0:02:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I emphasize the duality part first.\NLeave the devotional part to later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.12,0:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often that which is spiritually\Nnon-intigous
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,quotes itself as very spiritual and\Ntakes the form of a cult. We didn't talk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about cults.\NWe talked about when you got pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.68,0:03:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced\Nsomehow you become the target of all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.28,0:03:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's non-integrous to pull you\Ndown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.56,0:03:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be forewarned that such is\Nvery likely to happen. In fact, it will
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.59,0:03:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.\NAnd if you get very very evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the great forces of the universe\Nwill gang up and then you need a very
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.87,0:03:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced teacher. And the Buddha\Nremarked about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a seal from all sides by the\Ndemons, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In their most visible form though are\Ncults. And we should know what the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.36,0:03:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic of a cult is\Nso that I can die peacefully that I've
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.36,0:04:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,told you\Nmy last deathbed. I don't want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,some people wandering off. So\Nthe cult is led by a charismatic leader
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.36,0:04:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who's controlling. They're always\Ncontrolling and they try to control
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,private lives, what you should do with\Nyour money and your relationships and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.04,0:04:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your property.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.96,0:04:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nsex is allowed to the leader but not to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody else.\NTo avoid any responsibility, it's all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.19,0:04:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,blamed on a entity on the other side.\Nmaster somebody or other that way you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can avoid all responsibility because\Nmaster so and so said that you should
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.28,0:04:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,leave your wife she's holding you back\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.24,0:04:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So then there's titles, there's stratas,\Nthere's a commitment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.32,0:05:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's oaths and pledges. And\Nnever take an oath. I don't care how
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,mighty and it sounds.\NOaths and contracts etc can come back at
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.52,0:05:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a later lifetime and haunt haunt you and\Nyou won't know where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.56,0:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The oath in the contract is usually this\Num organization on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what's on the other side,\Nbut they're waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.80,0:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The cult\Nhas an exclusiveness. We're exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.28,0:05:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a name and their own inner\Nlanguage. And you're either one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or not.\NIf you're not one of them, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.63,0:05:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody. So they proilitize very\Nintensely, very intense proilitizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.40,0:06:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They become overzealous.\NThey want to sign you up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.03,0:06:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for a course. Of course, the courses\Nescalate over time. But anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then if you want to leave the cult,\Nthere's repercussions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes quite severe, even to the\Npoint of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you become anathema to the group.\NSo there's an us versus them. So whole
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole structure is dualistic\Nand there's great oo and a's about the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.03,0:06:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,leader.\NWhat is to be respected is the truth not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the leader.\NThose who want
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.91,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to make something out of the personality\Nof the leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.31,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no personality.\NThe personality, the persona is just a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,residual of what was and you reactivate\Nit in order to speak to groups. Now it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,has no reality. There is no person there\Nto oo and a over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.63,0:07:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What one is devoted to is truth.\NNot the avenue of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.08,0:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One is devoted to truth itself.\NThe speaker of truth may just is just a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.96,0:07:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,convenience.\NSo all this agilation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of some spiritual teacher is all the\Nglamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.12,0:07:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aware of it.\NGreet someone some somebody or other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.68,0:08:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody gif flex forget it.\NThe truth is the same. The self within
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you is the same as the self within the\Nteacher. No, it's not too different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.28,0:08:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not yourself and their self and\Ntheir self is better than yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same self.\NSo you worship the truth and not the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.16,0:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,personality\Nin whom it may through whom it may be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.03,0:08:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,spoken of. The personality is just a\Ntool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.27,0:08:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nothing at all\Nand it's eancent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It croakkes, dies, withers away.\Nuniverse gets rid of it. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,extraneous.\NThe dedication, the reverence is for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:09:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth itself.\NIf you have to sign up and become a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,member\Nand learn the language
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and follow\Nthe cult leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.88,0:09:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not the way to truth.\NIn spiritual naive, we think anything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.00,0:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,labeled spiritual is spiritual.\NAnd we think that the spiritual and the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,astral are one and the same. They are\Nnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the other discernment is between that\Nwhich is astral and that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,personal.\NEspecially
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,newagers get trapped by the by the\Nastral realms
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and channeling entities from the other\Nside etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All spiritual truth is spoken by people\Nin bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.51,0:10:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't see them, forget it.\NAll right. We said that we can stratify
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an artificial point of\Nobservation to stratify the level of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.72,0:10:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. We do that for\Ndescriptive purposes like we do
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.92,0:10:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,atmosphere\Nor depth below the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a convenience of description.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we could say these are levels of\NWell, this is a a new one that Lou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Fornier did\Nuh in which we put the two together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.27,0:10:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the population distribution of\Nthese levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the level of integrity\Nand these are the levels of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.64,0:11:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have an inverse one. These are\Nthe levels of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the levels of force\Nand the levels of power have an inverse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship with each other. All right?\NSo we don't want to get involved in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,cults, distractions,\Nthose are entertainments.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness on\Nthat we represent here in this domain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.16,0:11:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have their equivalent in non-physical\Ndomains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there we are.\NI've been following your chart and the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.92,0:11:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,more I study it, the worse I get.\NDoctor, what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Ntopsy turvy. Oh. Oh my god. Look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.39,0:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wiggliness there.\NThat which you see that level of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.56,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness within a body. That level\Nof consciousness exists also in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.48,0:12:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,astral realms without a physicality\Nbecause there's an infinite number of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,realms.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the motivations\Nof people as they go out of body are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be aligned with their level of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, people who are controlling\Nand seek power and desire to control
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.36,0:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,others when they go out of physicality\Nare going to stay the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.20,0:12:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the entities on the other\Nside are merely control freaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe your wife, wife of your children,\Nbuy horses, invest in this thought, sell
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.88,0:12:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your property, donate it to the group,\Nmeaning him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.48,0:13:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you want to avoid all that.\NAnd this is a pretty sophisticated group
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.95,0:13:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and most of you have avoided it.\NAnd one reason is because you got hooked
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on it.\NYou're still paying off
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.04,0:13:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the investments that Baba so and so told\Nyou to make from the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.63,0:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have to live in this world.\NSo it's okay for him to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, I want to just make sure\Nwe're aware what the traps are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you they're all fascinating.\NThey're fascinating. They're very
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.51,0:13:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting.\NAnd each one is representing a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.32,0:13:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,h\Nperceptual reality as they are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing it. And some of them\Nprobably legitimately believe that they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.39,0:14:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are representing some kind of truth to\Nthese unfortunate mortals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.80,0:14:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are higher celestial realms.\NThere's the lower astral. So there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.92,0:14:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,various cate categorizations of the\Nastral realms which correlate with the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness.\NAnd as you get over 200, there are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,realms of course that represent that as\Nwell. And you get into the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually the celestial realms.\NAnd some teachers coming from the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,celestial realms\Nare bonafideed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.88,0:14:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and useless.\NYou're not going to say anything that's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:15:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not available here.\NAnd the difficulty with following it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.32,0:15:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even if it's good advice is it's coming\Nfrom elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.76,0:15:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That reliance on my teacher on the other\Nside. The teacher is within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.56,0:15:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonuality means there's no this getting\Nit from a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.95,0:15:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness comes from within.\NAs you transcend the mind, as you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.19,0:15:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,dismantle the mind by removing its\Npositionalities upon which it thrives
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and survives, when you get over being\Nenamored of the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see it stupid.\NHumility. With humility, you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind doesn't know anything.\NAnd the reason the mind doesn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:16:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anything is it is not capable of\Nknowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.32,0:16:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is not capable\Nof knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.39,0:16:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than a ruler can tell you what\Nthe temperature is outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.19,0:16:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not.\NIt's suitable only for dealing in the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.36,0:16:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,perceptual world of form.\NWhere is our secret thing here? Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.24,0:16:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We keep this secret hidden from the\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.75,0:16:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for a small contribution,\Nwe will move you up to a second level of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.83,0:16:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,depth\Nand explain to you what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.24,0:17:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the secrets\Nis the other sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth has no secrets. That which claims\Na secret avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.07,0:17:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,God has no secrets. The sky has no\Nsecrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.95,0:17:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun shines with no secrets.\NAll is revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason for a secret is to have\Ncontrol over you so that I will get
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,something out of you in return for this\Nsecret which makes you special.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.96,0:17:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the attraction is one of specialness.\NThere are no secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.28,0:17:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no secrets to be known.\NAll truth stands revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.20,0:17:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It shines forth of its own.\NSo that which sells secrets, has secret
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.67,0:18:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,symbols and secret mantras and secret\Nsayings and secret handshakes, secret
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,mystical words and crap.\NThat's all facious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things are okay on the on the\Nway on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.91,0:18:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The only trouble is the power of\Nseduction is quite intense. Many of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,these entities have been at it for\Nmillennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.84,0:18:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Millennia\Nexpertise. It senses from another
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension exactly where you're\Nvulnerable and heads right for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they're expert. They're\Nexpert. They're at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody becomes an expert at what they\Ndo. So don't underrate the expertise of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that which would mislead you because it\Nis very expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.72,0:18:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing it's expert at is sounding\Nlike the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.32,0:19:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where its real danger lies.\NIt sounds like the convincingly real.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.03,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the third eye opens in the Buddha\Nbody, there's no way the average human
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can discern it.\NThat's where a teacher comes in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who can because it's it's obvious to the\Nteacher but not obvious to you. The
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher can point out what you can't see\Nyet. So you take his word for it until
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.12,0:19:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it yourself.\Nhappily. That's why I'm so pleased with
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.44,0:19:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,theologic test because\Nall of us, myself included,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,were vulnerable to spiritual seduction\Nand being misled
