Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the 30s. Every great thinker that ever\Nlived, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.96,0:35:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle and Plato and Uripides and\Ngoes all the way down to Freud, stops at
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.92,0:35:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud. So the work stops around 1900 or\Nso, but it calibrates at 475.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.07,0:35:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest thinkers of all of history\Ncalibrated at 475
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.76,0:35:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with the exception of Aristotle\Nwho was over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.48,0:35:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intellect will only take you so\Nfar for one reason. If you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.88,0:35:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the intellect of God, then study\Nepistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.20,0:35:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the nearest thing in philosophy\Nto spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.40,0:35:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is epistemology. Because epistemology\Ntakes you right to the door of how do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.35,0:36:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nthe whole subject of epistemology
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.00,0:36:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then takes the intellect as far as it\Ncan get to spiritual truth and then a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.24,0:36:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,jump has to be made. Mhm.\NThe techniques that we then follow are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.04,0:36:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not studying the written word\Nbut taking what we got from the written
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.96,0:36:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,word and making it operative within\Nourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.35,0:36:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then come to\Ndevotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.80,0:36:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,respect,\Nthe reverence for truth, the reverence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.04,0:36:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for the truth. It's not the teacher that\None reveres, but the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.64,0:36:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One reverses the truth.\NA reverence for the truth and a devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.88,0:36:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then carries you through the work that\Nit takes to go through the pathway of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.96,0:37:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,non-duality.\NThe three great yogas, selfless service,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.88,0:37:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,heart and mind are combined into one.\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.64,0:37:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the day, we look for no gain\Nfrom our work. We do it out of reverence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.24,0:37:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for life, out of reverence for our\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.40,0:37:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of non-duality\Nwhich becomes very demanding as it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.72,0:37:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,proceeds and we'll get into that this\Nafternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,then requires devotion\Nthe capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.07,0:37:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the devotion to the truth.\NSo one becomes devoted not to the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.40,0:38:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher but to the truth.\NThe teacher is only like a lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.59,0:38:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of the lighthouse is not the\Nlighthouse. The value of the lighthouse
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.68,0:38:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is the light going out to see. Not the\Nwe don't worship the lighthouse. You
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.88,0:38:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know what I'm saying?\NIsn't the lighthouse is going to save
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.40,0:38:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you? No. It's being able to see where\Nthe light is to guide yourself back to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.48,0:38:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shore.\NOne becomes increasingly motivated
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.40,0:38:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,um to and desiring of the truth until\Nfinally it almost becomes an obsession.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.11,0:38:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At first it's something you do now and\Nthen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.28,0:38:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have runs of it. You do a\Nweekend
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.04,0:38:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,retreat etc.\NThen you do another weekend retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.04,0:39:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile you read all the books, you go\Nto all the workshops
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.59,0:39:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and gradually a sort of a momentum\Nbuilds within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.20,0:39:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then finally desire to reach the\Ntruth becomes overwhelming. It becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.11,0:39:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the drivenness\Nand you will stop at nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.40,0:39:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the time to tell your family\Nthat your life is about to change
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.40,0:39:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they may think you've gone mad.\NThat's routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.88,0:39:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And people will walk out on everything.\NIt then becomes like an obsession,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.83,0:39:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a drivenness, a dedication.\NThere was an old movie
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.83,0:39:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost Horizon.\N>> Yeah. Who was it that plays in that with
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.80,0:39:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,me?\N>> Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.07,0:39:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\N>> Rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.20,0:40:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Rival.\N>> No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.28,0:40:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Coleman. Yes.\NWell, you remember I think I mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.88,0:40:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it in five words this horse even\N>> but having once experienced that high
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.72,0:40:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,energy I think we calibrated Shangerla\Nit I forget what it was it was quite
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,high but anyway once having experienced\Nit he tried going back into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.80,0:40:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried to function he was supposed to\Nhave some job with the British
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.00,0:40:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,government or something\Ntried to be satisfied with that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.68,0:40:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,less than what what he had experienced.\NBut he got caught by the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.40,0:40:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,energy and now\Nthrough all obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.44,0:40:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at the risk of death, physical death\Nitself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.68,0:40:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was driven to return to that state of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.04,0:41:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a number of people here in the\Nroom who've had that same inner
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.48,0:41:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.\NThey've had a sometimes after a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.52,0:41:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe in life, sometimes without\Nit, sometimes near-death experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.00,0:41:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it is. There's a number of\Npeople in the room and some I've seen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.40,0:41:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,personally and they experience that\Nincredible state. And now, oh Lord, how
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.07,0:41:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,could you have deserted me? It is gone.\NAnd I want to be back in that state
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.20,0:41:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,forever.\NThat's the beginning opening of the door
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.04,0:41:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,may open\Nand in the beginning it often closes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.11,0:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,again.\NRarely does it stay a permanency.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.80,0:41:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Most usually it reveals itself. One\Nexperiences the self in its full
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.80,0:42:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one experiences the oneness with\Ndivinity that that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.56,0:42:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely love infinite power beyond\Nall time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.00,0:42:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is not different than that which you are\Nexquisite unmistakable
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.64,0:42:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,always the same in everyone that it\Nhappens to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.04,0:42:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,no teacher has an exclus exclusive on\Nthe truth. Anybody who's ever
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.28,0:42:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced the self in its full\Nradiation has had exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.68,0:42:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,experience throughout all of time in all\Ncultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.64,0:42:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that varies from that is not\Nthe truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.59,0:42:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the presence of God\Nhas always been identical in all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.20,0:42:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cultures throughout thousands of years.\NNot statistically frequent
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.92,0:42:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but unmistakably identical.\NThere can be no other.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.16,0:43:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only the one and there can be\Nno other than the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.56,0:43:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Any description that varies from that\Ncannot be the truth because the truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.56,0:43:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,always the same.\NOnce in a while it's comical somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.72,0:43:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,will\NI get such funny letters
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.83,0:43:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know infer that you are what\Nplagiarizing somebody because a sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.64,0:43:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like something they read\Nsomewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.16,0:43:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It better sound like something you read\Nsomewhere else
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.48,0:43:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the experience of the truth is\Nalways the same whether
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.52,0:43:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the mood of Huda said that 600 BC or\Nwhat you know whether it's in the Vidas
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.64,0:44:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or Christianity or Buddhism or whatever\Nthat's all the cultural
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.31,0:44:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,trappings that go with\NSo that which is the absolute truth has
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.07,0:44:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,no cultural trappings.\NI say what is your spiritual lineage?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.20,0:44:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning I should trace teachers and\Nteachers back to the year something or
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.00,0:44:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other walking around usually in the\NMiddle East in some place or India or
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.88,0:44:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,some strange foreign place.\NNow the spirit of truth is the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.52,0:44:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of God within in this instant. It has\Nnothing to do with whatever happened in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.83,0:44:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,history.\NWhatever happened in history is totally
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.35,0:44:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,boring.\NA curiosity perhaps when you first start
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.56,0:44:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,studying\Nwhether anything or anyone ever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.11,0:44:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced before is totally\Nirrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.96,0:45:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the reality of no\Nbe like asking a bird where did you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.40,0:45:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that you were a bird?\NI just am a bird for God's sake. Anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.40,0:45:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,can see that. So\Nall doubt is removed by
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.48,0:45:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of self as this infinite\Npresence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.80,0:45:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that is doubtful is coming from\Nthe ego that is resisting its own
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.52,0:45:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,disillusion,\Nits own dissolution and is hoping it can
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.04,0:45:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,find a conundrum that will puzzle you so\Nit can go on. Gotcha there, duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.80,0:45:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThere is nothing to argue about with the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.16,0:45:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,truth because it is not arguable. The\Nreason is it takes no form. To argue
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.92,0:46:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with something, it has to have form.\NYou see, context has no form. All form.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.35,0:46:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's arguable about religion is when\Nit is expressed in dogma,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.31,0:46:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,enthusiastic doctrine, then it can be\Nargued with.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.11,0:46:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you don't do that, you can't\Nargue with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.28,0:46:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only express a limitation\Nbut that limitation that that religion
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.11,0:46:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,expresses is a limitation of its own\Ninnate truth and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.80,0:46:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So that which is truly\Nspiritual then
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.16,0:46:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,grants perfect freedom.\NThere is no dogma to be followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.96,0:46:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No excommunication is possible.\NThere is no membership that can be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.28,0:46:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,revoked.\NNo titles that can be withdrawn, no
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.24,0:47:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,possessions that can be you know see\Nspirits of truth then is open and free.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.28,0:47:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to join. There's no dues\Nto pay. There are no language to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.31,0:47:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reverence do anybody.\NThere is however a common devotion to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.92,0:47:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth. What holds a true spiritual\Ngroup group together
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.07,0:47:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is all of us are profoundly devoted and\Nworship the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.64,0:47:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God within\Nwhich expresses itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.76,0:47:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh thee I adore. Oh Lord,\Na profound devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.11,0:47:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nthe radical truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.96,0:47:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the pathway of radical\Ndevotional
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.07,0:48:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,non-duality.\NActually
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.52,0:48:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the pathway to mystic isn't it?\NThat is the pathway to mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.80,0:48:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is found within when all\Nbarriers to it are removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.88,0:48:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The commonality in this group is\Ndevotion to the innate truth of God
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.31,0:48:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.48,0:48:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the recognition\Nand awareness that that reality can be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.83,0:48:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectively verified\Nif all the barriers to it are removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.24,0:48:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the lectures then is how\Nto remove the barriers
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.44,0:48:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so that that which is within shines\Nforth of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.80,0:48:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun shines forth when the clouds are\Nremoved from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:49:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You have reductions to truth.\NSo truth is not something one acquires
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.07,0:49:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or gets. You don't get enlightened or\Nanything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.04,0:49:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When all barriers are removed, the sun\Nshines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.11,0:49:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,equally on all.\NThe energy of that truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.59,0:49:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what the teacher transmits\Nnot to one's mental bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.76,0:49:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but to one's higher spiritual bodies.\NIt's the vibration of the higher
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.07,0:49:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual bodies that go get activated\Nby the frequency of that vibration which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.88,0:49:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,comes of the certainty of the\Nabsoluteness of the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.07,0:49:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for which I give thanks oh lord. Amen.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.64,0:50:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what unites a true spiritual group is\Nthe absolute commitment to the pursuit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.44,0:50:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth\Nand we
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.40,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,support each other in that endeavor.\NSometimes it takes the strength and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,conviction of others who have done it\Nand say yes that is the way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.76,0:50:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This becomes very true\Nas I say the spiritual work eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.83,0:50:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,takes you to a point where the spiritual\Nthe power the spiritual inspiration now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.24,0:50:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,forces you. You see it isn't that you're\Nchoosing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.76,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't your desiringness of a higher\Nstate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins to pull you up. You see,\Nit's like the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.72,0:50:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the density of the ocean becomes so\Nintense that you like a quirk are forced
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.31,0:50:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,up in it. You would like to congratulate\Nyourself that you've chosen to become
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.88,0:51:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual.\NFact is the other way around. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.07,0:51:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,chosen you, brother.\NI want you. And it begins to pull you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.83,0:51:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the closer you get to the magnet,\Nthe more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.31,0:51:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the iron filing is attracted until\Nfinally it's undeniable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.52,0:51:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you remove enough barriers, you are\Npulled to it whether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.40,0:51:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nby transcending identification with the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.31,0:51:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,mind, what you do\Nas each thing arises, one lets it go
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.92,0:51:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally the mind is silent.\NYou notice that at all times you think
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.55,0:51:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind is busy and you can't conquer\Nit and all this. Don't try and conquer
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.48,0:51:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind. Just don't identify with it.\NSo where do you look? You look to that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.68,0:52:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is just a priority to mind\Nat all times. The majority, the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,part of your mind is silent. Did you\Never know that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.83,0:52:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind is silent all the time?\NA little bitty part of your mind is busy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.16,0:52:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about this and that, but the\Nmajor portion of it is still in silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.76,0:52:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not saying anything.\NYou're only paying attention to the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.07,0:52:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,noisy part here. At all times, your mind\Nis silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.92,0:52:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to notice how your mind is\Nsilent is that although your intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.88,0:52:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is listening to what's being said, there\Nis within you the awareness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.35,0:52:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of this room and where we are\Nin Sedona and Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.64,0:52:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a silent part of you that just\Naccepts that the sky is here without
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.72,0:53:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking sky.\NSpace is here. Silence is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.48,0:53:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But the ego wants you to focus on it so\Nit can survive. As you withdraw your
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.88,0:53:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,energy back from the in being entranced\Nand enamored of the mind and its going
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.40,0:53:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on,\Nyou become there is at all times the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.59,0:53:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,majority of your mind is silent.\NEven the thinkingness which is going on
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.92,0:53:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,here\Ndoes not interfere with the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.76,0:53:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because you cannot interfere with the\Nsilence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.52,0:53:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're out in the woods, the woods\Nare silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.76,0:53:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A bird makes a song.\NDid the bird destroy the silence? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.31,0:53:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The silence is still there.\NThe bird sound is superimposed against
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.83,0:54:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the background of the silence or else\Nyou couldn't hear the bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.40,0:54:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is the silence which is so the\Nsilence is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.72,0:54:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,immune to interruption\Njust as the silent area of your mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.96,0:54:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,always silent.\NWhat is your mind doing when it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.11,0:54:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking? It's being silent.\NPeople panic. Jesus, my mother suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.72,0:54:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,went dead. I didn't think of anything.\NDoctor, do you think I'm well? Am I
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.52,0:54:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,getting Alzheimer's?\NNo, the silence is the presence within
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.31,0:54:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on the level of consciousness.\NAnd out of your consciousness comes the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.88,0:54:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness which is witnessing and\Nregistering the thinkingness. But it's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.92,0:54:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all coming out of a silence.\NThis silence prevails right before the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.35,0:55:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thought arises.\NYou see the the mind thinks in linear
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.48,0:55:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,terms. So it thinks in the sentence the\Ncat is the dog is chasing the cat up the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.40,0:55:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,tree that this is a linear sequence of\Nthoughts. The cat no the dog is chasing
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.72,0:55:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat up the tree.\NHe sees a causal sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.64,0:55:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, if you study your mind through\Nintrospective meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.76,0:55:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see that the thoughts arise\Nthis this way. The out of nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.35,0:55:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the dog is chasing the cat up the tree.\NEvery single thought arises from
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.83,0:55:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness.\NEvery single thought is an original
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.52,0:55:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,creation.\NSuperimposed upon that is a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.11,0:56:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualization\Nthat we call reason or logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.59,0:56:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said the space in which the\Nvoid by that he meant the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.88,0:56:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of the self can be recognized\Nis between thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.83,0:56:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's right prior to thoughts.\NWe've just discussed it endlessly,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.59,0:56:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha and I.\NI said he agreed. He said, "It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.96,0:56:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,between thoughts. It's just prior\Nthoughts." No, it's the translation from
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.04,0:56:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,various languages and all. Besides, you\Nwent there to hear the Buddha lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.76,0:56:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, he was that what he's trying to\Nconvey is there's only one truth to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.68,0:56:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,convey two truths. You see it isn't that\Nthe space is between the thoughts or
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.11,0:56:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,between prior to the thoughts but in\Nboth of course conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.72,0:57:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you watch as your mind just starts\Nto think you'll see that just before the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.55,0:57:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,instant that thought started there was\Nnothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.40,0:57:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought comes out of nothing.\NYou discover that you're close to being
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.88,0:57:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,home.\NYou begin to identify with the so silent
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.07,0:57:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness out of which each thought\Narises.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.92,0:57:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is closest to your reality is\Nthe silent field out of which the song
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.44,0:57:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the bird arises.\NThe silent mind is present within you at
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.07,0:57:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all times. It's present right this\Ninstant.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.35,0:57:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only listening with a little\Nbitty part of your mind. The majority of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.20,0:57:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind is silent.\NIsn't that amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.55,0:57:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> One identifies progressively then with
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.76,0:58:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with with the field\Nthe context
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.88,0:58:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are is the context.\NAt a more advanced level, you see that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.76,0:58:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the context all include context includes\Ncontent as well. But at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.79,0:58:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,forget about content.\NYou're the context out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.28,0:58:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it all arises,\Nout of the energy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.59,0:58:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you become devoted to\NM
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.07,0:58:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the discernment of this quality of\Nsilence within
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.28,0:58:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,by the letting go of everything that\Nstands in its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.20,0:59:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes progressively silent\Nand then there comes a moment where the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.88,0:59:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,only thing left\Nis you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.11,0:59:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing left to be surrendered\Nis the sense of self which you've always
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.92,0:59:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,identified as self\Nand you realize that you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.04,0:59:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender that also.\NAt the final doorway to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.40,0:59:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then stands death.\NDeath as you understand it. Death as you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.11,0:59:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,have experienced it.\NDeath as it is believed in. Because if
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.24,0:59:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you think you are is\Nlife itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.07,0:59:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender that to God\Nmeans to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.64,1:00:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, the training you had\Nas a warrior and many a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.31,1:00:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to die for a greater\Ncause now comes forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.52,1:00:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to have been able to commit Harry Kerry,\Nthe willingness to die for one's belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.88,1:00:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then comes the great terror of death\Nbecause all the times you've died in
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.92,1:00:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,previous lifetimes with a joke.\NWhaml, you're out of body and life is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.28,1:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,better than it was before. I'll tell\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.96,1:00:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've never experienced death.\NNobody has experienced that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.79,1:00:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one and only time you can\Nactually die.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.59,1:00:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the knowingness that what you\Nare facing is absolute death.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.28,1:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then arises the terror of\Nnothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.00,1:01:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If that which I believe and am committed\Nto as myself, if I surrender that, I
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.92,1:01:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will become nothing.\NThere is the fear of death and the fear
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.44,1:01:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the void.\NAt that point, at that point, those who
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.72,1:01:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,have been through there, the energy of\Nthose who have been through that point
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.79,1:01:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will come to you\Nand you will remember,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.64,1:01:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,walk straight ahead. No matter what, no\Nmatter how severe the fear,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.52,1:01:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest fear of all, walk through\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.88,1:01:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the terror lasts for an ungodly\Nminute
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.48,1:01:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and one has made it through. So the\Ngreat beings that have walked through
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.48,1:01:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there and when you're there, you'll see\Nwho was there. You know who was there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.24,1:02:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and who turned back. The majority turned\Nback. 85% turned back.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.35,1:02:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I want to make the\Ninstruction clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.68,1:02:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In thy name, oh Lord,\Nat the moment of death,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.52,1:02:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,die for God\Nand walk through the fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.40,1:02:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then stands the glory unfolding,\Na radiance so magnificent, so beyond all
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.04,1:02:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehension,\Nbeyond that which is humanly knowable
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.11,1:02:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because at that point you stop being\Nhuman. You walk beyond humanness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.31,1:02:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of divinity.\NThere is one basic saying in Zen that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.35,1:03:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,one can rely on completely\Nand that is to walk through all fear no
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.55,1:03:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,matter what.\NWalk through all fear committed to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.83,1:03:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth no matter what.\NFirst of all make sure that's spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.20,1:03:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,truth.\NSecondly, make sure
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.00,1:03:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that you know this from the knowingness\Nof that which has accomplished it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.79,1:03:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It better be a teacher who has been\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.79,1:03:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Know it with a concrete faith that that\Nwithin you which is dedicated to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.52,1:03:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching God is what's brought you to\Nthe point of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.48,1:03:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time then\None says
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.03,1:04:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for thee oh Lord God do I lay down my\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.44,1:04:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So those words will be with you. Amen.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.35,1:04:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And um\Ntherefore I have fulfilled my
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.31,1:04:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,role as a teacher.\NI've told you the whole story.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.35,1:04:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. We'll break for lunch. We'll\Nbe back in an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.76,1:04:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we wanted all the staff, volunteer\Noffice staff, uh we wanted all the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.55,1:04:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,volunteer staff\Nand office staff
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.59,1:05:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and those who have been of great\Nassistance to us, contribute
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.00,1:05:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Karen,\N>> they shall remain anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.31,1:05:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would you like to do, my dear?\N>> Um, the hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.76,1:05:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh my goodness. Somebody could help you\Ndo that. In fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.64,1:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yeah,\N>> somebody could volunteer to help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.24,1:05:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody could volunteer to help you.\NWhere's a volunteer? Take one out. Help
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.00,1:05:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, sweetheart.\N>> That's what you can do. Just say help
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.79,1:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself. Oh,\N>> help yourself. That's the way you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.68,1:05:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,volunteer\N>> now. Don't you wish you'd volunteered?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.52,1:05:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Actually, so many people have\Nwanted to help and we are overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.83,1:06:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with gratitude and some sit in the\Naudience who have made great
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.76,1:06:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,contributions and you should come up\Nahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.35,1:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. And you get one too.\NNow we could take turns. We could all go
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.00,1:06:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out in the audience and the whole\Naudience could come up here
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.92,1:06:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because without you, who would we be?\NNobody, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.28,1:06:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\N>> And what do we got there? Oh my
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.28,1:07:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,goodness. Don't we have to take these\Nthings off?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.76,1:07:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days\Na year.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.24,1:07:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you so much, my sweetheart.\N>> Everyone's applause.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.03,1:07:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right, you sit down. I'm going to\Nput him in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.31,1:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, we want to thank you all from the\Nbottom of our heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.20,1:07:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You've all been of such wonderment to us\Nand we love you all and adore you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.03,1:07:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I just wanted to acknowledge them\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.96,1:07:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledge all of you for being here\Nand making your contribution to us by
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.40,1:07:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,being here. Thank you.\NOkay. So, we're resume. Thank you so
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.11,1:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,much.\NThanks to Sedona Creative Life Center
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.88,1:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for, you know, supplying such a\Nbeautiful place
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.92,1:08:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowing us to meet here.\NIn the contract, it says we won't spray
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.96,1:08:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,perfume or drop flower petals around.\NWe did not mean to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.44,1:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They did it of their own.
